        "materials_required": [
            "Tripod with device attachment",
            "Varied brush sizes (1/4 in flat brush will be invaluable)",
            "Sand (color(s) can be varied)"
        ],
        "description": "This project guides you through creating a stop motion animation using sand. You'll manipulate sand on a flat surface, photograph each adjustment, and then compile the images into a short animated video.",
        "steps": [
            "Set up your device on a tripod with the device attachment. Ensure that neither the tripod nor the device is moved during filming to prevent shaky images.",
            "Pour approximately 3 tablespoons of sand into the center of your field of view.",
            "Shape the sand into a circle using your hands.",
            "Use a paintbrush to manipulate the sand into an initial image.",
            "Continue using the paintbrush to refine the shape of your image. Don't worry about stray grains of sand, as they can add to the effect.",
            "Photograph the sand image using the stop motion animation app after each adjustment, ensuring no unwanted objects (like fingers or the brush) are in the frame.",
            "Transform your image by adding further details, photographing after each change.",
            "Remember that more pictures with smaller changes will result in a smoother animation.",
            "Continue adding details to your image, using both the brush and your hands to add or remove portions of sand.",
            "Once you have a collection of images, edit them in the Stop Motion Animation editor. You can add a theme, voice over, or sound effects.",
            "Adjust the speed of the images.",
            "Preview your work to check on your edits.",
            "Share your creation."
        ]
